I&#39;m not entirely sure why TypeScript cannot narrow the type down in your case. I got it working here on [TypeScript Playground.][1]

Beware that the type of your Actions need to be strings which are instantly assigned a value with either no type definition `export const USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED = &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39;` or with the specific string as type definition like this `export const USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED: &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39; = &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39;`. 

```
export const USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED = &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39;; // Correct
export const USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED: &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39; = &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39;; // Correct
export const USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED: string = &#39;USER_CONVERSATION_RECEIVED&#39;; // Wrong
```

It seems that TypeScript infers your nested property to be of type string (as you found out). If you use a const on a primitive type string, the value can never be changed - thus, the type can be narrowed down from string to &#39;UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED&#39;. If you nest that inside an object, the object reference itself is always the same - but you can change properties of that object. Thus, TypeScript has to assume the type is string (and cannot narrow it down more), since it could be changed at some point (because it is not readonly by default).

A workaround would be, obviously, to not nest it. As an alternative, you can provide typescript with a more narrow type, though that would look quite verbose:

```
export const MESSAGING_ACTIONS: { 
    USER: {
        UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED: &#39;UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED&#39;
    }
} = {
    USER:{
        UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED: &#39;UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED&#39;
    }
}

// or with an interface

export interface MessagingActions {
    USER: {
        UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED: &#39;UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED&#39;
    }
}

export const MESSAGING_ACTIONS:MessagingActions = {
    USER:{
        UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED: &#39;UNSEEN_MESSAGE_RECEIVED&#39;
    }
}
```


